"PHY"	"""Orange-bellied Trogon"" T.c. aurantiiventris is a member of the Middle American puella subspecies group (DaCosta & Klicka 2008).Â  NACC and Dickinson (2003) treat as separate species with note that it might be a color morph of T.collaris. Current NACC treatment wrongly separates T. aurantiiventris and lumps puella with collaris (DaCosta & Klicka 2008, TIF). STET current treatment of inclusive collaris."
